<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Elytral punctures and coloration: a in rows in deep striae, Pachybrachis luctuosus b confused in basal half, in rows in apical half, Pachybrachis calcaratus c all confused, Pachybrachis hepaticus d confused and mottled, Pachybrachis spumarius e vittate with marginal vitta interrupted, Pachybrachis bivattatus f black, margined with yellow, Pachybrachis nigriconis carbonarius g entirely black, Pachybrachis luridus." , "Habitus 9 b. Dorsal habitus of Pachybrachis nigricornis carbonarius. Almost black. Scale bar, 1 mm." , "Figure 6. Pronotum: a reddish, with close-up of marginal bead, Pachybrachis bivittatus b mottled, Pachybrachis spumarius c with black M-mark, Pachybrachis m-nigrum d almost black, Pachybrachis nigricornis carbonarius." , "Habitus 9 c. Dorsal habitus of Pachybrachis nigricornis carbonarius. Yellow at edge of elytra. Scale bar, 1 mm." , "Habitus 9 a. Dorsal habitus of Pachybrachis nigricornis difficilis. Scale bar, 1 mrn." , "Map 9. The known distribution of Pachybrachis nigricornis in eastern Canada. SR - Saguenay River." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20917" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20918" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20863" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20916" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20944" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20864" .

